. Named after the 
<typeStatus box="[527,575,1432,1456]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="K. Viets, 1935" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1935" box="[688,1034,1468,1493]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albaxona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexapora">
<emphasis box="[688,830,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">A. hexapora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[851,1026,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 14, Tropische Binnengewasser, 113 pp." type="book" year="1935">
K. Viets, 
<number box="[969,1026,1468,1493]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1935.0">1935</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Java in the more elongated idiosoma. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lundblad, 1971" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1971" box="[275,693,1503,1528]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albaxona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="javanica">
<emphasis box="[275,493,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Albaxona javanica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad" box="[508,693,1503,1528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" refString="Lundblad, O. (1971) Weitere Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Fliesswassermilben Javas. Arkiv for Zoologie, 23, 293 - 359. [Serie 2]" type="journal article" year="1971">
Lundblad, 
<number box="[637,693,1504,1528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Java shares an elongated idiosoma, but is smaller, the postocularia are closer to each other and dgl- 
<number box="[656,668,1540,1565]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="3.0">3</number>
and - 
<number box="[730,745,1540,1564]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
are located more anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,853,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,999,1600]" box="[199,853,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1575,1600]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</emphasis>
Borneo; known only from the locus typicus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
